        <h2 style="text-align:center;font-size: 22px;color:cyan;">Karnataka Crab Curry</h2>
        <img style="padding-left:225px;width:400px;height:400px" src="https://anuthefoodiconfood.files.wordpress.com/2021/12/img_20211230_123717.jpg" alt="Karnataka Crab Curry">

        <div id="en">
            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Ingredients:</p>
            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px"> For Marinating the Crab:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li> 4-6 crab clusters (cleaned and washed)</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
                <li> Salt to taste</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px">For the Masala Paste:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li> 1 cup grated fresh coconut</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon mustard seeds,1 teaspoon cumin seeds, 4-5 fenugreek seeds</li>
                <li> 6-8 dried red chilies (adjust to taste)</li>
                <li> 4-5 peppercorns</li>
                <li> A small piece of tamarind (soaked in water)</li>
                <li> 1 onion, finely chopped</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px">For the Curry:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li> 2 tablespoons oil</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon mustard seeds</li>
                <li> A pinch of asafoetida (hing)</li>
                <li> Curry leaves</li>
                <li> Salt to taste</li>
                <li> Water</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Instructions:</p>
            <br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">1. Marinate the Crab:</li><ul>
                <li> In a large bowl, mix the crab clusters with turmeric powder and salt.</li>
                <li>Allow them to marinate for at about 15-20 minutes.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">2. Prepare Masala Paste:</li><ul>
                <li>
                    In a blender or food processor, combine grated coconut, mustard seeds, dried red chilies, cumin seeds,
                    <br /> fenugreek seeds, peppercorns, and the soaked tamarind piece.<br />
                <li> Add a little water and blend into a smooth paste.</li>
                <li> Add the finely chopped onion to the paste and blend briefly to mix.</li>
            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">3. Cook the Crab:</li><ul>
                <li> Heat oil in a deep pan over medium-high heat.</li>
                <li> Add mustard seeds and let them splutter.</li>
                <li> Add a pinch of asafoetida (hing) and curry leaves.</li>
                <li> Carefully add the marinated crab clusters and sauté for a few minutes.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">4. Add the Masala Paste:</li><ul>
                <li> Pour the prepared masala paste over the crab.</li>
                <li> Mix well to coat the crab evenly with the masala.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">5. Add Water:</li><ul>
                <li> Add enough water to cover the crab and achieve your desired curry consistency.</li>
                <li> Add salt to taste and stir.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">6. Cook the Curry:</li><ul>
                <li> Cover the pan and let the crab curry simmer over medium-low heat for about 15-20 minutes,</li>
                or until the crab is fully cooked and the flavors meld.
                <br />

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">7. Serve:</li><ul>
                <li> Once the crab is cooked and the curry has thickened, remove from heat.</li>
                <li> Serve the Crab Curry hot with steamed rice.</li>

            </ul><p style="color:orange;font-size:20px">Enjoy the delightful flavors of your homemade crab curry!</p>
